# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-doctor

Model/effort: Sonnet / medium.

Diagnoses the environment and running app, reports what is wrong, and applies only
clearly-safe fixes — escalating anything risky rather than guessing.

## Steps
1. OPEN-lite: read the latest `05-logs/` entry for context; state the symptom or scope of
   the health check.
2. Check the environment: toolchain versions, required services, configuration presence
   (not secret values), and dependency health.
3. Try to run the app the way the project runs it; capture errors and logs.
4. Diagnose root causes and rank them by impact.
5. Apply only safe fixes (e.g. reinstalling deps, recreating local scaffolding). Leave
   risky or ambiguous changes as recommendations; never touch secrets or live config.
6. Report findings and actions. If a fix changed brain state, append a continuity entry
   and push.

## Done when
The environment and app are diagnosed, safe fixes are applied, and remaining risks are
reported as clear recommendations.
